": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:chapter/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:chapter/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 73}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under section 75A or 75B may— make provision about notices to be given, evidence to be produced and other procedures to be followed by employees and employers; make provision requiring employers or employees to keep records; make provision for the consequences of failure to give notices, to produce evidence, to keep records or to comply with other procedural requirements; make provision for the consequences of failure to act in accordance with a notice given by virtue of paragraph (a); make special provision for cases where an employee has a right which corresponds to a right under this Chapter and which arises under his contract of employment or otherwise; make provision modifying the effect of Chapter 2 of Part 14 (calculation of a week’s pay) in relation to an employee who is or has been absent from work on ordinary or additional adoption leave; make provision applying, modifying or excluding an enactment, in such circumstances as may be specified and subject to any conditions specified, in relation to a person entitled to ordinary or additional adoption leave; make different provision for different cases or circumstances.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:chapter/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:chapter/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 74}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where a person who is, or has been, an employee satisfies the conditions in subsection (2) below, he shall be entitled in accordance with the following provisions of this Part to payments to be known as “statutory adoption pay”.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 75}, {"enrichment_value" : "A person may not elect to receive statutory adoption pay if— he has elected in accordance with section 171ZB above to receive statutory paternity pay, or where the child is, or is expected to be, placed for adoption with him as a member of a married couple and his spouse is a person to whom the conditions in subsection (2) above apply, his spouse has elected to receive statutory adoption pay.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 76}, {"enrichment_value" : "A person’s entitlement to statutory adoption pay shall not be affected by the placement, or expected placement, for adoption of more than one child as part of the same arrangement.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 77}, {"enrichment_value" : "A person shall be entitled to payments of statutory adoption pay only if— he gives the person who will be liable to pay it notice of the date from which he expects the liability to pay him statutory adoption pay to begin; and the notice is given at least 28 days before that date or, if that is not reasonably practicable, as soon as is reasonably practicable.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 78}, {"enrichment_value" : "The notice shall be in writing if the person who is liable to pay the statutory adoption pay so requests.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 79}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by regulations— provide that subsection (2)(b), (c) or (d) above shall have effect subject to prescribed modifications in such cases as may be prescribed; provide that subsection (6) above shall not have effect, or shall have effect subject to prescribed modifications, in such cases as may be prescribed; impose requirements about evidence of entitlement; specify in what circumstances employment is to be treated as continuous for the purposes of this section; provide that a person is to be treated for the purposes of this section as being employed for a continuous period of at least 26 weeks where— he has been employed by the same employer for at least 26 weeks under two or more separate contracts of service; and those contracts were not continuous; provide for amounts earned by a person under separate contracts of service with the same employer to be aggregated for the purposes of this section; provide that— the amount of a person’s earnings for any period, or the amount of his earnings to be treated as comprised in any payment made to him or for his benefit, shall be calculated or estimated for the purposes of this section in such manner and on such basis as may be prescribed and that for that purpose payments of a particular class or description made or falling to be made to or by a person shall, to such extent as may be prescribed, be disregarded or, as the case may be, be deducted from the amount of his earnings; make provision about elections for statutory adoption pay.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 80}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations shall make provision as to a former employer’s liability to pay statutory adoption pay to a person in any case where the former employee’s contract of service with him has been brought to an end by the former employer solely, or mainly, for the purpose of avoiding liability for statutory adoption pay.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 81}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may, with the concurrence of the Board, by regulations specify circumstances in which, notwithstanding this section, liability to make payments of statutory adoption pay is to be a liability of the Board.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 82}, {"enrichment_value" : "Statutory adoption pay shall be payable at such fixed or earnings-related weekly rate as the Secretary of State may prescribe by regulations, which may prescribe different kinds of rate for different cases.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 83}, {"enrichment_value" : "Statutory adoption pay shall be payable, subject to the provisions of this Part of this Act, in respect of each week during a prescribed period (“the adoption pay period”) of a duration not exceeding 26 weeks.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 84}, {"enrichment_value" : "A person shall not be liable to pay statutory adoption pay to another in respect of any week during any part of which the other works under a contract of service with him.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 85}, {"enrichment_value" : "Except in such cases as may be prescribed, statutory adoption pay shall not be payable to a person in respect of any week during any part of which he works for any employer who is not liable to pay him statutory adoption pay.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 86}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by regulations specify circumstances in which there is to be no liability to pay statutory adoption pay in respect of a week.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 87}, {"enrichment_value" : "Any agreement shall be void to the extent that it purports— to exclude, limit or otherwise modify any provision of this Part of this Act, or to require an employee or former employee to contribute (whether directly or indirectly) towards any costs incurred by his employer or former employer under this Part of this Act.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 88}, {"enrichment_value" : "For the avoidance of doubt, any agreement between an employer and an employee authorising any deductions from statutory adoption pay which the employer is liable to pay to the employee in respect of any period shall not be void by virtue of subsection (1)(a) above if the employer— is authorised by that or another agreement to make the same deductions from any contractual remuneration which he is liable to pay in respect of the same period, or would be so authorised if he were liable to pay contractual remuneration in respect of that period.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 89}, {"enrichment_value" : "Except as may be prescribed, a day which falls within the adoption pay period shall not be treated as a day of incapacity for work for the purposes of determining, for this Act, whether it forms part of a period of incapacity for work for the purposes of incapacity benefit.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 90}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations may provide that in prescribed circumstances a day which falls within the adoption pay period shall be treated as a day of incapacity for work for the purposes of determining entitlement to the higher rate of short-term incapacity benefit or to long-term incapacity benefit.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 91}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations may provide that an amount equal to a person’s statutory adoption pay for a period shall be deducted from any such benefit in respect of the same period and a person shall be entitled to such benefit only if there is a balance after the deduction and, if there is such a balance, at a weekly rate equal to it.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 92}, {"enrichment_value" : "Subject to subsections (5) and (6) below, any entitlement to statutory adoption pay shall not affect any right of a person in relation to remuneration under any contract of service (“contractual remuneration”).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 93}, {"enrichment_value" : "any contractual remuneration paid to a person by an employer of his in respect of a week in the adoption pay period shall go towards discharging any liability of that employer to pay statutory adoption pay to him in respect of that week; and", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[5]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[5]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 94}, {"enrichment_value" : "any statutory adoption pay paid by an employer to a person who is an employee of his in respect of a week in the adoption pay period shall go towards discharging any liability of that employer to pay contractual remuneration to him in respect of that week.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[5]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[5]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 95}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations may make provision as to payments which are, and those which are not, to be treated as contractual remuneration for the purposes of subsections (4) and (5) above.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 96}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may with the concurrence of the Treasury make regulations modifying any provision of this Part of this Act in such manner as he thinks proper in its application to any person who is, has been or is to be— employed on board any ship, vessel, hovercraft or aircraft; outside Great Britain at any prescribed time or in any prescribed circumstances; or in prescribed employment in connection with continental shelf operations, as defined in section 120(2) above.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 97}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1) above may, in particular, provide— for any provision of this Part of this Act to apply to any such person, notwithstanding that it would not otherwise apply; for any such provision not to apply to any such person, notwithstanding that it would otherwise apply; for excepting any such person from the application of any such provision where he neither is domiciled nor has a place of residence in any part of Great Britain; for the taking of evidence, for the purposes of the determination of any question arising under any such provision, in a country or territory outside Great Britain, by a British consular official or such other person as may be determined in accordance with the regulations.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 98}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations may provide— for cases where a person who falls within the definition in subsection (2) above is not to be treated as an employee for the purposes of this Part of this Act, and for cases where a person who would not otherwise be an employee for the purposes of this Part of this Act is to be treated as an employee for those purposes.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 99}, {"enrichment_value" : "Without prejudice to any other power to make regulations under this Part of this Act, regulations may specify cases in which, for the purposes of this Part of this Act or of such provisions of this Part of this Act as may be prescribed— two or more employers are to be treated as one; two or more contracts of service in respect of which the same person is an employee are to be treated as one.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 100}, {"enrichment_value" : "In this Part, except sections 171ZN and 171ZP, “week” means a period of 7 days beginning with Sunday or such other period as may be prescribed in relation to any particular case or class of cases.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 101}, {"enrichment_value" : "For the purposes of this Part of this Act, a person’s normal weekly earnings shall, subject to subsection (8) below, be taken to be the average weekly earnings which in the relevant period have been paid to him or paid for his benefit under the contract of service with the employer in question.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 102}, {"enrichment_value" : "For the purposes of subsection (6) above, “earnings” and “relevant period” shall have the meanings given to them by regulations.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 103}, {"enrichment_value" : "In such cases as may be prescribed, a person’s normal weekly earnings shall be calculated in accordance with regulations.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 104}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where— in consequence of the establishment of one or more National Health Service trusts under Part 1 of the National Health Service and Community Care Act  1990 (c. 19)  or the National Health Service (Scotland) Act  1978 (c. 29) , a person’s contract of employment is treated by a scheme under that Part or Act as divided so as to constitute two or more contracts, or an order under paragraph 23(1) of Schedule 5A to the National Health Service Act  1977 (c. 49)  provides that a person’s contract of employment is so divided, regulations may make provision enabling the person to elect for all of those contracts to be treated as one contract for the purposes of this Part of this Act or such provisions of this Part of this Act as may be prescribed.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[9]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[9]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 105}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (9) above may prescribe— the conditions that must be satisfied if a person is to be entitled to make such an election; the manner in which, and the time within which, such an election is to be made; the persons to whom, and the manner in which, notice of such an election is to be given; the information which a person who makes such an election is to provide, and the persons to whom, and the time within which, he is to provide it; the time for which such an election is to have effect; which one of the person’s employers under two or more contracts is to be regarded for the purposes of statutory adoption pay as his employer under the contract.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[10]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[10]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 106}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under any of subsections (4) to (10) above must be made with the concurrence of the Board.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[12]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[12]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 107}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by regulations provide for this Part to have effect in relation to cases which involve adoption, but not the placement of a child for adoption under the law of any part of the United Kingdom, with such modifications as the regulations may prescribe.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[9]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[9]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 108}, {"enrichment_value" : "For the purposes of the Inland Revenue Regulation Act  1890 (c. 21) , except sections 21, 22 and 35, everything that relates to statutory paternity pay or statutory adoption pay shall be taken to relate to inland revenue; and the expressions “in relation to inland revenue”, “Collector of Inland Revenue” and “Officer of Inland Revenue” are to be read accordingly.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 109}, {"enrichment_value" : "The reference in section 4(1) of that Act (appointment of collectors, officers and other persons) to collecting, receiving, managing and accounting for inland revenue shall be taken to include a reference to paying and managing statutory paternity pay and statutory adoption pay.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 110}, {"enrichment_value" : "In any declaration for the purposes of section 6 of the Taxes Management Act  1970 (c. 9)  (declarations on taking office), whether made before or after the commencement of this section, the reference to an offence relating to inland revenue shall be taken to include a reference to an offence relating to statutory paternity pay or statutory adoption pay.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 111}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State shall by regulations make provision for the payment by employers of statutory paternity pay and statutory adoption pay to be funded by the Board to such extent as the regulations may specify.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 112}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1) shall— make provision for a person who has made a payment of statutory paternity pay or statutory adoption pay to be entitled, except in such circumstances as the regulations may provide, to recover an amount equal to the sum of— the aggregate of such of those payments as qualify for small employers' relief; and an amount equal to 92 per cent of the aggregate of such of those payments as do not so qualify; and include provision for a person who has made a payment of statutory paternity pay or statutory adoption pay qualifying for small employers' relief to be entitled, except in such circumstances as the regulations may provide, to recover an additional amount equal to the amount to which the person would have been entitled under section 167(2)(b) of the Social Security Contributions and Benefits Act 1992 (corresponding provision for statutory maternity pay) had the payment been a payment of statutory maternity pay.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 113}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1) may, in particular— make provision for funding in advance as well as in arrear; make provision for funding, or the recovery of amounts due under provision made by virtue of subsection (2)(b), by means of deductions from such amounts for which employers are accountable to the Board as the regulations may provide, or otherwise; make provision for the recovery by the Board of any sums overpaid to employers under the regulations.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 114}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where in accordance with any provision of regulations under subsection (1) an amount has been deducted from an employer’s contributions payments, the amount so deducted shall (except in such cases as the Secretary of State may by regulations provide) be treated for the purposes of any provision made by or under any enactment in relation to primary or secondary Class 1 contributions— as having been paid (on such date as may be determined in accordance with the regulations), and as having been received by the Board, towards discharging the employer’s liability in respect of such contributions.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 115}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under this section must be made with the concurrence of the Board.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 116}, {"enrichment_value" : "In this section, “contributions payments”, in relation to an employer, means any payments which the employer is required, by or under any enactment, to make in discharge of any liability in respect of primary or secondary Class 1 contributions.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 117}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may make regulations with respect to the payment by employers of statutory paternity pay and statutory adoption pay.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 118}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1) may, in particular, include provision— about the records to be kept by employers in relation to payments of statutory paternity pay and statutory adoption pay, including the length of time for which they are to be retained; for the production of wages sheets and other documents and records to officers of the Board for the purpose of enabling them to satisfy themselves that statutory paternity pay and statutory adoption pay have been paid and are being paid, in accordance with the regulations, to employees who are entitled to them; for requiring employers to provide information to employees (in their itemised pay statements or otherwise); for requiring employers to make returns to the Board containing such particulars with respect to payments of statutory paternity pay and statutory adoption pay as the regulations may provide.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 119}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1) must be made with the concurrence of the Board.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 120}, {"enrichment_value" : "In section 8(1) (which lists social security matters in relation to which decisions shall be for an officer of the Board)— in paragraph (f) (issues relating to entitlement to statutory sick pay or statutory maternity pay), for “or statutory maternity pay” there is substituted “, statutory maternity pay, statutory paternity pay or statutory adoption pay”, in paragraph (g) (other issues relating to those matters) for the words from “under Part” to the end there is substituted “under Parts 11 to 12ZB of the Social Security Contributions and Benefits Act 1992 (statutory sick pay, statutory maternity pay, statutory paternity pay and statutory adoption pay)”, and after that paragraph there is inserted— ga to make any decision that falls to be made under regulations under section 7 of the Employment Act 2002 (funding of employers' liabilities to make payments of statutory paternity or adoption pay), . to make any decision that falls to be made under regulations under section 7 of the Employment Act 2002 (funding of employers' liabilities to make payments of statutory paternity or adoption pay),", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 121}, {"enrichment_value" : "Information to which this section applies may be supplied— to the Secretary of State or the Department, or to a person providing services to the Secretary of State or the Department, for use for the purposes of functions relating to social security, child support or war pensions.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[9]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[9]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 135}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by regulations make provision enabling an officer of the Board authorised by the Board for the purposes of this section to require persons of a description specified in the regulations to provide, or produce for inspection, within such period as the regulations may require, such information or documents as the officer may reasonably require for the purpose of ascertaining whether statutory paternity pay or statutory adoption pay is or was payable to or in respect of any person.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 122}, {"enrichment_value" : "The descriptions of person which may be specified by regulations under subsection (1) include, in particular— any person claiming to be entitled to statutory paternity pay or statutory adoption pay, any person who is, or has been, the spouse or partner of such a person as is mentioned in paragraph (a), any person who is, or has been, an employer of such a person as is mentioned in paragraph (a), any person carrying on an agency or other business for the introduction or supply to persons requiring them of persons available to do work or to perform services, and any person who is a servant or agent of any such person as is specified in paragraphs (a) to (d).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 123}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1) must be made with the concurrence of the Board.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 124}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where a person— fails to produce any document or record, provide any information or make any return, in accordance with regulations under section 8, or fails to provide any information or document in accordance with regulations under section 10, he shall be liable to the penalties mentioned in subsection (2) below (subject to subsection (4)).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 125}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where a person fails to keep records in accordance with regulations under section 8Ì, he shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding £3,000.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 126}, {"enrichment_value" : "Subject to subsection (5), no penalty shall be imposed under subsection (2) or (3) at any time after the failure concerned has been remedied.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 127}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where, in the case of any employee, an employer refuses or repeatedly fails to make payments of statutory paternity pay or statutory adoption pay in accordance with any regulations under section 8, the employer shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding £3,000.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 128}, {"enrichment_value" : "Section 118(2) of the Taxes Management Act  1970 (c. 9)  (extra time for compliance etc) shall apply for the purposes of subsections (1), (3) and (6) as it applies for the purposes of that Act.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 129}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where a person fraudulently or negligently— makes any incorrect statement or declaration in connection with establishing entitlement to statutory paternity pay, or provides any incorrect information or document of a kind mentioned in regulations under section 10(1) so far as relating to statutory paternity pay, he shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding £300.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 130}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where a person fraudulently or negligently— makes any incorrect statement or declaration in connection with establishing entitlement to statutory adoption pay, or provides any incorrect information or document of a kind mentioned in regulations under section 10(1) so far as relating to statutory adoption pay, he shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding £3,000.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[8]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, 