for such purposes and to such extent as may be prescribed”, and", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 139}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may make regulations making provision, in relation to the right to return under subsection (4)(c) above, about— seniority, pension rights and similar rights; terms and conditions of employment on return.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 140}, {"enrichment_value" : "Statutory maternity pay shall be payable to a woman— at the earnings-related rate, in respect of the first 6 weeks in respect of which it is payable; and at whichever is the lower of the earnings-related rate and such weekly rate as may be prescribed, in respect of the remaining portion of the maternity pay period.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 141}, {"enrichment_value" : "The weekly rate prescribed under subsection (1)(b) above must not be less than the weekly rate of statutory sick pay for the time being specified in section 157(1) above or, if two or more such rates are for the time being so specified, the higher or highest of those rates.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 142}, {"enrichment_value" : "A woman shall be entitled to payments of statutory maternity pay only if— she gives the person who will be liable to pay it notice of the date from which she expects his liability to pay her statutory maternity pay to begin; and the notice is given at least 28 days before that date or, if that is not reasonably practicable, as soon as is reasonably practicable.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 143}, {"enrichment_value" : "in paragraph (e) of subsection (9), for sub-paragraphs (i) to (iii) there is substituted “in such cases as may be prescribed”; and", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:paragraph[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:paragraph[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 144}, {"enrichment_value" : "provide that subsection (4) above shall not have effect, or shall have effect subject to prescribed modifications, in such cases as may be prescribed;", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:paragraph[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:paragraph", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:paragraph[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:paragraph", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 145}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations shall make provision for the payment by employers of statutory maternity pay to be funded by the Commissioners of Inland Revenue to such extent as may be prescribed.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 146}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1) shall— make provision for a person who has made a payment of statutory maternity pay to be entitled, except in prescribed circumstances, to recover an amount equal to the sum of— the aggregate of such of those payments as qualify for small employers' relief; and an amount equal to 92 per cent of the aggregate of such of those payments as do not so qualify; and include provision for a person who has made a payment of statutory maternity pay qualifying for small employers' relief to be entitled, except in prescribed circumstances, to recover an additional amount, determined in such manner as may be prescribed— by reference to secondary Class 1 contributions paid in respect of statutory maternity pay; by reference to secondary Class 1 contributions paid in respect of statutory sick pay; or by reference to the aggregate of secondary Class 1 contributions paid in respect of statutory maternity pay and secondary Class 1 contributions paid in respect of statutory sick pay.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 147}, {"enrichment_value" : "For the purposes of this section “small employer”, in relation to a woman’s maternity pay period, shall have the meaning assigned to it by regulations, and, without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing, any such regulations— may define that expression by reference to the amount of a person’s contributions payments for any prescribed period; and if they do so, may in that connection make provision for the amount of those payments for that prescribed period— to be determined without regard to any deductions that may be made from them under this section or under any other enactment or instrument; and in prescribed circumstances, to be adjusted, estimated or otherwise attributed to him by reference to their amount in any other prescribed period.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 148}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1) may, in particular, make provision— for funding in advance as well as in arrear; for funding, or the recovery of amounts due under provision made by virtue of subsection (2)(b), by means of deductions from such amounts for which employers are accountable to the Commissioners of Inland Revenue as may be prescribed, or otherwise; for the recovery by the Commissioners of Inland Revenue of any sums overpaid to employers under the regulations.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 149}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where in accordance with any provision of regulations under subsection (1) an amount has been deducted from an employer’s contributions payments, the amount so deducted shall (except in such cases as may be prescribed) be treated for the purposes of any provision made by or under any enactment in relation to primary or secondary Class 1 contributions— as having been paid (on such date as may be determined in accordance with the regulations), and as having been received by the Commissioners of Inland Revenue, towards discharging the employer’s liability in respect of such contributions.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 150}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under this section must be made with the concurrence of the Commissioners of Inland Revenue.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 151}, {"enrichment_value" : "In this section “contributions payments”, in relation to an employer, means any payments which the employer is required, by or under any enactment, to make in discharge of any liability in respect of primary or secondary Class 1 contributions.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 152}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations shall make provision for the payment by employers of statutory maternity pay to be funded by the Commissioners of Inland Revenue to such extent as may be prescribed.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 153}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1) shall— make provision for a person who has made a payment of statutory maternity pay to be entitled, except in prescribed circumstances, to recover an amount equal to the sum of— the aggregate of such of those payments as qualify for small employers' relief; and an amount equal to 92 per cent of the aggregate of such of those payments as do not so qualify; and include provision for a person who has made a payment of statutory maternity pay qualifying for small employers' relief to be entitled, except in prescribed circumstances, to recover an additional amount, determined in such manner as may be prescribed— by reference to secondary Class 1 contributions paid in respect of statutory maternity pay; by reference to secondary Class 1 contributions paid in respect of statutory sick pay; or by reference to the aggregate of secondary Class 1 contributions paid in respect of statutory maternity pay and secondary Class 1 contributions paid in respect of statutory sick pay.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 154}, {"enrichment_value" : "For the purposes of this section “small employer”, in relation to a woman’s maternity pay period, shall have the meaning assigned to it by regulations, and, without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing, any such regulations— may define that expression by reference to the amount of a person’s contributions payments for any prescribed period; and if they do so, may in that connection make provision for the amount of those payments for that prescribed period— to be determined without regard to any deductions that may be made from them under this section or under any other enactment or instrument; and in prescribed circumstances, to be adjusted, estimated or otherwise attributed to him by reference to their amount in any other prescribed period.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 155}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1) may, in particular, make provision— for funding in advance as well as in arrear; for funding, or the recovery of amounts due under provision made by virtue of subsection (2)(b), by means of deductions from such amounts for which employers are accountable to the Commissioners of Inland Revenue as may be prescribed, or otherwise; for the recovery by the Commissioners of Inland Revenue of any sums overpaid to employers under the regulations.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 156}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where in accordance with any provision of regulations under subsection (1) an amount has been deducted from an employer’s contributions payments, the amount so deducted shall (except in such cases as may be prescribed) be treated for the purposes of any provision made by or under any enactment in relation to primary or secondary Class 1 contributions— as having been paid (on such date as may be determined in accordance with the regulations), and as having been received by the Commissioners of Inland Revenue, towards discharging the employer’s liability in respect of such contributions.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 157}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under any provision of this section shall be made by the Secretary of State.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 158}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under this section must be made with the concurrence of the Commissioners of Inland Revenue.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 159}, {"enrichment_value" : "In this section “contributions payments”, in relation to an employer, means any payments which the employer is required, by or under any enactment, to make in discharge of any liability in respect of primary or secondary Class 1 contributions.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[9]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[9]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 160}, {"enrichment_value" : "Employment tribunal procedure regulations may include provision— for the award of costs or expenses; for the award of any allowances payable under section 5(2)(c) or (3).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 161}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1) may include provision authorising an employment tribunal to have regard to a person’s ability to pay when considering the making of an award against him under such regulations.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 162}, {"enrichment_value" : "Employment tribunal procedure regulations may include provision for authorising an employment tribunal— to disallow all or part of the costs or expenses of a representative of a party to proceedings before it by reason of that representative’s conduct of the proceedings; to order a representative of a party to proceedings before it to meet all or part of the costs or expenses incurred by a party by reason of the representative’s conduct of the proceedings; to order a representative of a party to proceedings before it to meet all or part of any allowances payable by the Secretary of State under section 5(2)(c) or (3) by reason of the representative’s conduct of the proceedings.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 163}, {"enrichment_value" : "Employment tribunal procedure regulations may also include provision for taxing or otherwise settling the costs or expenses referred to in subsection (1)(a) or (1B)(b) (and, in particular in England and Wales, for enabling the amount of such costs to be assessed by way of detailed assessment in a county court).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 164}, {"enrichment_value" : "Employment tribunal procedure regulations may include provision for authorising an employment tribunal to order a party to proceedings before it to make a payment to any other party in respect of time spent in preparing that other party’s case.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 165}, {"enrichment_value" : "Employment tribunal procedure regulations may authorise the determination of proceedings without any hearing in such circumstances as the regulations may prescribe.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 177}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1) may include provision authorising an employment tribunal to have regard to a person’s ability to pay when considering the making of an order against him under such regulations.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 166}, {"enrichment_value" : "If employment tribunal procedure regulations include— provision of the kind mentioned in subsection (1), and provision of the kind mentioned in section 13(1)(a), they shall also include provision to prevent an employment tribunal exercising its powers under both kinds of provision in favour of the same person in the same proceedings.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 167}, {"enrichment_value" : "Appeal Tribunal procedure rules may include provision for the award of costs or expenses.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 168}, {"enrichment_value" : "Rules under subsection (1) may include provision authorising the Appeal Tribunal to have regard to a person’s ability to pay when considering the making of an award against him under such rules.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 169}, {"enrichment_value" : "Appeal Tribunal procedure rules may include provision for authorising the Appeal Tribunal— to disallow all or part of the costs or expenses of a representative of a party to proceedings before it by reason of that representative’s conduct of the proceedings; to order a representative of a party to proceedings before it to meet all or part of the costs or expenses incurred by a party by reason of the representative’s conduct of the proceedings.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 170}, {"enrichment_value" : "Appeal Tribunal procedure rules may also include provision for taxing or otherwise settling the costs or expenses referred to in subsection (1) or (3)(b) (and, in particular in England and Wales, for enabling the amount of such costs to be assessed by way of detailed assessment in the High Court).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 171}, {"enrichment_value" : "for postponing fixing a time and place for a hearing, or postponing a time fixed for a hearing, for such period as may be determined in accordance with the regulations for the purpose of giving an opportunity for the proceedings to be settled by way of conciliation and withdrawn, and", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subparagraph", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subparagraph", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 172}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where employment tribunal procedure regulations include provision postponing the fixing of a time and place for a hearing for the purpose of giving an opportunity for the proceedings to be settled by way of conciliation and withdrawn, subsection (2) shall have effect from the end of the postponement to confer a power on the conciliation officer, instead of imposing a duty.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 173}, {"enrichment_value" : "In section 19 of that Act (conciliation procedure), paragraph (c) (which requires employment tribunal procedure regulations, in relation to conciliation cases, to include provision postponing the hearing to give an opportunity for conciliation) shall cease to have effect.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 174}, {"enrichment_value" : "If employment tribunal procedure regulations include provision postponing the fixing of a time and place for a hearing for the purpose of giving an opportunity for the proceedings to be settled by way of conciliation and withdrawn, they shall also include provision for the parties to proceedings to which the provision for postponement applies to be notified that the services of a conciliation officer may no longer be available to them after the end of the postponement.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 175}, {"enrichment_value" : "Employment tribunal procedure regulations may— authorise the Secretary of State to prescribe, or prescribe requirements in relation to, any form which is required by such regulations to be used for the purpose of instituting, or entering an appearance to, proceedings before employment tribunals, authorise the Secretary of State to prescribe requirements in relation to documents to be supplied with any such form, and make provision about the publication of anything prescribed under authority conferred by virtue of this subsection.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 176}, {"enrichment_value" : "Employment tribunal procedure regulations may include provision— enabling the President to make directions about the procedure of employment tribunals, including directions about the exercise by tribunals of powers under such regulations, for securing compliance with such directions, and about the publication of such directions.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 178}, {"enrichment_value" : "Employment tribunal procedure regulations may, instead of providing for any matter, refer to provision made or to be made about that matter by directions made by the President.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 179}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1)(b), so far as relating to striking out, may not provide for striking out on a ground which does not apply outside a pre-hearing review.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[2]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 180}, {"enrichment_value" : "Schedule 2 (which sets out the statutory dispute resolution procedures) shall have effect.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 181}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by order— amend Schedule 2; make provision for the Schedule to apply, with or without modifications, as if— any individual of a description specified in the order who would not otherwise be an employee for the purposes of the Schedule were an employee for those purposes; and a person of a description specified in the order were, in the case of any such individual, the individual’s employer for those purposes.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 182}, {"enrichment_value" : "Before making an order under this section, the Secretary of State must consult the Advisory, Conciliation and Arbitration Service.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 183}, {"enrichment_value" : "Every contract of employment shall have effect to require the employer and employee to comply, in relation to any matter to which a statutory procedure applies, with the requirements of the procedure.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 184}, {"enrichment_value" : "Subsection (1) shall have effect notwithstanding any agreement to the contrary, but does not affect so much of an agreement to follow a particular procedure as requires the employer or employee to comply with a requirement which is additional to, and not inconsistent with, the requirements of the statutory procedure.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 185}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may for the purpose of this section by regulations make provision about the application of the statutory procedures.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 186}, {"enrichment_value" : "the non-completion of the statutory procedure was wholly or mainly attributable to failure by the employee— to comply with a requirement of the procedure, or to exercise a right of appeal under it, it must, subject to subsection (4), reduce any award which it makes to the employee by 10 per cent, and may, if it considers it just and equitable in all the circumstances to do so, reduce it by a further amount, but not so as to make a total reduction of more than 50 per cent.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:paragraph[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:paragraph[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 187}, {"enrichment_value" : "If, in the case of proceedings to which this section applies, it appears to the employment tribunal that— the claim to which the proceedings relate concerns a matter to which one of the statutory procedures applies, the statutory procedure was not completed before the proceedings were begun, and the non-completion of the statutory procedure was wholly or mainly attributable to failure by the employer to comply with a requirement of the procedure, it must, subject to subsection (4), increase any award which it makes to the employee by 10 per cent and may, if it considers it just and equitable in all the circumstances to do so, increase it by a further amount, but not so as to make a total increase of more than 50 per cent.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 188}, {"enrichment_value" : "The duty under subsection (2) or (3) to make a reduction or increase of 10 per cent does not apply if there are exceptional circumstances which would make a reduction or increase of that percentage unjust or inequitable, in which case the tribunal may make no reduction or increase or a reduction or increase of such lesser percentage as it considers just and equitable in all the circumstances.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 189}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where an award falls to be adjusted under this section and under section 38, the adjustment under this section shall be made before the adjustment under that section.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 190}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may for the purposes of this section by regulations— make provision about the application of the statutory procedures; make provision about when a statutory procedure is to be taken to be completed; make provision about what constitutes compliance with a requirement of a statutory procedure; make provision about circumstances in which a person is to be treated as not subject to, or as having complied with, such a requirement; make provision for a statutory procedure to have effect in such circumstances as may be specified by the regulations with such modifications as may be so specified; make provision about when an employee is required to exercise a right of appeal under a statutory procedure.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 191}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by order— amend Schedule 3 for the purpose of— adding a jurisdiction to the list in that Schedule, or removing a jurisdiction from that list; make provision, in relation to a jurisdiction listed in Schedule 3, for this section not to apply to proceedings relating to claims of a description specified in the order; make provision for this section to apply, with or without modifications, as if— any individual of a description specified in the order who would not otherwise be an employee for the purposes of this section were an employee for those purposes, and a person of a description specified in the order were, in the case of any such individual, the individual’s employer for those purposes.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 192}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employee shall not present a complaint to an employment tribunal under a jurisdiction to which this section applies if— it concerns a matter in relation to which the requirement in paragraph 6 or 9 of Schedule 2 applies, and the requirement has not been complied with.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 193}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employee shall not present a complaint to an employment tribunal under a jurisdiction to which this section applies if— it concerns a matter in relation to which the requirement in paragraph 6 or 9 of Schedule 2 has been complied with, and less than 28 days have passed since the day on which the requirement was complied with.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 194}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employee shall not present a complaint to an employment tribunal under a jurisdiction to which this section applies if— it concerns a matter in relation to which the requirement in paragraph 6 or 9 of Schedule 2 has been complied with, and the day on which the requirement was complied with was more than one month after the end of the original time limit for making the complaint.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 195}, {"enrichment_value" : "In such circumstances as the Secretary of State may specify by regulations, an employment tribunal may direct that subsection (4) shall not apply in relation to a particular matter.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 196}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employment tribunal shall be prevented from considering a complaint presented in breach of subsections (2) to (4), but only if— the breach is apparent to the tribunal from the information supplied to it by the employee in connection with the bringing of the proceedings, or the tribunal is satisfied of the breach as a result of his employer raising the issue of compliance with those provisions in accordance with regulations under section 7 of the Employment Tribunals Act  1996 (c. 17)  (employment tribunal procedure regulations).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 197}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may for the purposes of this section by regulations— make provision about the application of the procedures set out in Part 2 of Schedule 2; make provision about what constitutes compliance with paragraph 6 or 9 of that Schedule; make provision about circumstances in which a person is to be treated as having complied with paragraph 6 or 9 of that Schedule; make provision for paragraph 6 or 9 of that Schedule to have effect in such circumstances as may be specified by the regulations with such modificiations as may be so specified.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 198}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by order— amend, repeal or replace any of subsections (2) to (4); amend Schedule 4; make provision for this section to apply, with or without modifications, as if— any individual of a description specified in the order who would not otherwise be an employee for the purposes of this section were an employee for those purposes, and a person of a description specified in the order were, in the case of any such individual, the individual’s employer for those purposes.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 199}, {"enrichment_value" : "Before making an order under subsection (8)(a), the Secretary of State must consult the Advisory, Conciliation and Arbitration Service.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[9]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[9]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 200}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may, in relation to a jurisdiction listed in Schedule 3 or 4, by regulations make provision about the time limit for beginning proceedings in respect of a claim concerning a matter to which a statutory procedure applies.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 201}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under this section may, in particular— make provision extending, or authorising the extension of, the time for beginning proceedings, make provision about the exercise of a discretion to extend the time for beginning proceedings, or make provision treating proceedings begun out of time as begun within time.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 202}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employee who is dismissed shall be regarded for the purposes of this Part as unfairly dismissed if— one of the procedures set out in Part 1 of Schedule 2 to the Employment Act 2002 (dismissal and disciplinary procedures) applies in relation to the dismissal, the procedure has not been completed, and the non-completion of the procedure is wholly or mainly attributable to failure by the employer to comply with its requirements.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 203}, {"enrichment_value" : "Subject to subsection (1), failure by an employer to follow a procedure in relation to the dismissal of an employee shall not be regarded for the purposes of section 98(4)(a) as by itself making the employer’s action unreasonable if he shows that he would have decided to dismiss the employee if he had followed the procedure.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 204}, {"enrichment_value" : "For the purposes of this section, any question as to the application of a procedure set out in Part 1 of Schedule 2 to the Employment Act 2002, completion of such a procedure or failure to comply with the requirements of such a procedure shall be determined by reference to regulations under section 31 of that Act.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 205}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where— an employee is regarded as unfairly dismissed by virtue of section 98A(1) (whether or not his dismissal is unfair or regarded as unfair for any other reason), and an order is made in respect of the employee under section 113, the employment tribunal shall, subject to subsection (6), also make an award of four weeks' pay to be paid by the employer to the employee.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 206}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employment tribunal shall not be required to make an award under subsection (5) if it considers that such an award would result in injustice to the employer.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 207}, {"enrichment_value" : "There shall be deducted from any award under subsection (1) the amount of any award made under section 112(5) at the time of the order under section 113.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 208}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where the amount of the compensatory award falls to be calculated for the purposes of an award under section 117(3)(a), there shall be deducted from the compensatory award any award made under section 112(5) at the time of the order under section 113.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[5]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[5]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 209}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where— an employee is regarded as unfairly dismissed by virtue of section 98A(1) (whether or not his dismissal is unfair or regarded as unfair for any other reason), an award of compensation falls to be made under section 112(4), and the amount of the award under section 118(1)(a), before any reduction under section 122(3A) or (4), is less than the amount of four weeks' pay, the employment tribunal shall, subject to subsection (1B), increase the award under section 118(1)(a) to the amount of four weeks' pay.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[6]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[6]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 210}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employment tribunal shall not be required by subsection (1A) to increase the amount of an award if it considers that the increase would result in injustice to the employer.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[6]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[6]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 211}, {"enrichment_value" : "In section 3 of the Employment Rights Act  1996 (c. 18)  (note about disciplinary rules and procedures), subsections (3) and (4) (exemptions for undertakings with less than 20 employees) shall cease to have effect.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 212}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employer’s duty under section 1 in relation to any matter shall be treated as met if the document given to the employee contains information which, were the document in the form of a statement under that section, would meet the employer’s obligation under that section in relation to that matter.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 213}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employer’s duty under section 3 shall be treated as met if the document given to the employee contains information which, were the document in the form of a statement under section 1 and the information included in the form of a note, would meet the employer’s obligation under section 3.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 214}, {"enrichment_value" : "For the purposes of this section a document to which subsection (1)(a) applies shall be treated, in relation to information in respect of any of the matters mentioned in section 1(4), as specifying the date on which the document is given to the employee as the date as at which the information applies.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 215}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where subsection (2) applies in relation to any matter, the date on which the document by virtue of which that subsection applies is given to the employee shall be the material date in relation to that matter for the purposes of section 4(1).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 216}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where subsection (3) applies, the date on which the document by virtue of which that subsection applies is given to the employee shall be the material date for the purposes of section 4(1) in relation to the matters of which particulars are required to be given under section 3.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 217}, {"enrichment_value" : "The reference in section 4(6) to an employer having given a statement under section 1 shall be treated as including his having given a document by virtue of which his duty to give such a statement is treated as met.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 218}, {"enrichment_value" : "A document in the form of a contract of employment or letter of engagement given by an employer to an employee before the beginning of the employee’s employment with the employer shall, when the employment begins, be treated for the purposes of section 7A as having been given at that time.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[3]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 219}, {"enrichment_value" : "If in the case of proceedings to which this section applies— the employment tribunal finds in favour of the employee, but makes no award to him in respect of the claim to which the proceedings relate, and when the proceedings were begun the employer was in breach of his duty to the employee under section 1(1) or 4(1) of the Employment Rights Act  1996 (c. 18)  (duty to give a written statement of initial employment particulars or of particulars of change), the tribunal must, subject to subsection (5), make an award of the minimum amount to be paid by the employer to the employee and may, if it considers it just and equitable in all the circumstances, award the higher amount instead.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 220}, {"enrichment_value" : "If in the case of proceedings to which this section applies— the employment tribunal makes an award to the employee in respect of the claim to which the proceedings relate, and when the proceedings were begun the employer was in breach of his duty to the employee under section 1(1) or 4(1) of the Employment Rights Act 1996, the tribunal must, subject to subsection (5), increase the award by the minimum amount and may, if it considers it just and equitable in all the circumstances, increase the award by the higher amount instead.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 221}, {"enrichment_value" : "The amount of a week’s pay of an employee shall— be calculated for the purposes of this section in accordance with Chapter 2 of Part 14 of the Employment Rights Act  1996 (c. 18) , and not exceed the amount for the time being specified in section 227 of that Act (maximum amount of week’s pay).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 222}, {"enrichment_value" : "For the purposes of Chapter 2 of Part 14 of the Employment Rights Act 1996 as applied by subsection (6), the calculation date shall be taken to be— if the employee was employed by the employer on the date the proceedings were begun, that date, and if he was not, the effective date of termination as defined by section 97 of that Act.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 223}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by order— amend Schedule 5 for the purpose of— adding a jurisdiction to the list in that Schedule, or removing a jurisdiction from that list; make provision, in relation to a jurisdiction listed in Schedule 5, for this section not to apply to proceedings relating to claims of a description specified in the order; make provision for this section to apply, with or without modifications, as if— any individual of a description specified in the order who would not otherwise be an employee for the purposes of this section were an employee for those purposes, and a person of a description specified in the order were, in the case of any such individual, the individual’s employer for those purposes.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 224}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where an award of compensation for unfair dismissal falls to be— reduced or increased under section 31 of the Employment Act 2002 (non-completion of statutory procedures), or increased under section 38 of that Act (failure to give statement of employment particulars), the adjustment shall be in the amount awarded under section 118(1)(b) and shall be applied immediately before any reduction under section 123(6) or (7).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[3]/ns:section[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[3]/ns:hcontainer[3]/ns:section[1]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 225}, {"enrichment_value" : "a person who considers that she may have a claim under section 1 above is referred to as “the complainant”, and", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 226}, {"enrichment_value" : "a person against whom the complainant may decide to make, or has made, a complaint under section 2(1) or 7A(3) above is referred to as “the respondent”.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 227}, {"enrichment_value" : "With a view to helping a complainant to decide whether to institute proceedings and, if she does so, to formulate and present her case in the most effective manner, the Secretary of State shall by order prescribe— forms by which the complainant may question the respondent on any matter which is or may be relevant, and forms by which the respondent may if he so wishes reply to any questions.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 228}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where the complainant questions the respondent (whether in accordance with an order under subsection (2) above or not), the question and any reply by the respondent (whether in accordance with such an order or not) shall, subject to the following provisions of this section, be admissible as evidence in any proceedings under section 2(1) or 7A(3) above.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 229}, {"enrichment_value" : "the respondent deliberately and without reasonable excuse omitted to reply within such period as the Secretary of State may by order prescribe, or", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[4]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[4]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 230}, {"enrichment_value" : "If in any proceedings under section 2(1) or 7A(3) above it appears to the employment tribunal that the complainant has questioned the respondent (whether in accordance with an order under subsection (2) above or not) and that— the respondent deliberately and without reasonable excuse omitted to reply within such period as the Secretary of State may by order prescribe, or the respondent’s reply is evasive or equivocal, it may draw any inference which it considers it just and equitable to draw, including an inference that the respondent has contravened a term modified or included by virtue of the complainant’s equality clause or corresponding term of service.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 231}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where the Secretary of State questions an employer in relation to whom he may decide to make, or has made, a reference under section 2(2) above, the question and any reply by the employer shall, subject to the following provisions of this section, be admissible as evidence in any proceedings under that provision.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 232}, {"enrichment_value" : "the employer deliberately and without reasonable excuse omitted to reply within such period as the Secretary of State may by order prescribe, or", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[6]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[6]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 233}, {"enrichment_value" : "A penalty determined under paragraph 1 above shall be due and payable at the end of the period of thirty days beginning with the date of the issue of the notice of determination.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 296}, {"enrichment_value" : "If in any proceedings on a reference under section 2(2) above it appears to the employment tribunal that the Secretary of State has questioned the employer to whom the reference relates and that— the employer deliberately and without reasonable excuse omitted to reply within such period as the Secretary of State may by order prescribe, or the employer’s reply is evasive or equivocal, it may draw any inference which it considers it just and equitable to draw, including an inference that the employer has contravened a term modified or included by virtue of the equality clause of the woman, or women, as respects whom the reference is made.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 234}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by order— prescribe the period within which questions must be duly served in order to be admissible under subsection (3) or (5) above, and prescribe the manner in which a question, and any reply, may be duly served.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 235}, {"enrichment_value" : "An order under this section may make different provision for different cases.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[10]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[10]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 236}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employer shall permit an employee of his who is— a member of an independent trade union recognised by the employer, and a learning representative of the trade union, to take time off during his working hours for any of the following purposes.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 237}, {"enrichment_value" : "Only one notice under subsection (4)(b) may be given in respect of any one employee.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 238}, {"enrichment_value" : "If an employer is required to permit an employee to take time off under subsection (1), he shall also permit the employee to take time off during his working hours for the following purposes— undergoing training which is relevant to his functions as a learning representative, and where the trade union has in the last six months given the employer notice under subsection (4)(b) in relation to the employee, undergoing such training as is mentioned in subsection (4)(a).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 239}, {"enrichment_value" : "The amount of time off which an employee is to be permitted to take under this section and the purposes for which, the occasions on which and any conditions subject to which time off may be so taken are those that are reasonable in all the circumstances having regard to any relevant provision of a Code of Practice issued by ACAS or the Secretary of State.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[8]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 240}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employee may present a complaint to an employment tribunal that his employer has failed to permit him to take time off as required by this section.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[9]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[9]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 241}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employer shall permit an employee of his who is a member of an independent trade union recognised by the employer in respect of that description of employee to take time off during his working hours for the purpose of having access to services provided by a person in his capacity as a learning representative of the trade union.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 242}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by order made by statutory instrument amend section 168A for the purpose of changing the purposes for which an employee may take time off under that section.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[6]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[6]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 243}, {"enrichment_value" : "No order may be made under subsection (3) unless a draft of the order has been laid before and approved by resolution of each House of Parliament.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[6]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[6]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 244}, {"enrichment_value" : "Timing and location of meetings must be reasonable.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[3]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[3]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 343}, {"enrichment_value" : "A Code containing practical guidance— on the time off to be permitted to a trade union learning representative in accordance with section 168A (time off for training and carrying out functions as a learning representative), on the training that is sufficient to enable a trade union learning representative to carry on the activities mentioned in section 168A(2) (activities for which time off is to be permitted), or on any of the matters referred to in section 199(2), shall not be issued unless the draft has been approved by a resolution of each House of Parliament; and if it is so approved, ACAS shall issue the Code in the form of the draft.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[8]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[8]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 245}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by order amend subsection (3) so as to add to the conditions specified in that subsection such conditions as he may specify in the order.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:subsection", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 246}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State shall make regulations— for the purpose of securing that employees in fixed-term employment are treated, for such purposes and to such extent as the regulations may specify, no less favourably than employees in permanent employment, and for the purpose of preventing abuse arising from the use of successive periods of fixed-term employment.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 247}, {"enrichment_value" : "The regulations may— specify classes of employee who are to be taken to be, or not to be, in fixed-term employment; specify classes of employee who are to be taken to be, or not to be, in permanent employment; specify circumstances in which employees in fixed-term employment are to be taken to be, or not to be, treated less favourably than employees in permanent employment; specify circumstances in which periods of fixed-term employment are to be taken to be, or not to be, successive; specify circumstances in which fixed-term employment is to have effect as permanent employment; make provision which has effect in relation to employees in fixed-term employment generally or provision which has effect only in relation to specified classes of employee in fixed-term employment.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 248}, {"enrichment_value" : "The regulations may— confer jurisdiction (including exclusive jurisdiction) on employment tribunals; provide for specified obligations not to apply in specified circumstances; make provision about notices or information to be given, evidence to be produced and other procedures to be followed; amend, apply with or without modifications, or make provision similar to any provision of— the Employment Rights Act  1996 (c. 18)  (including, in particular, Parts 5, 10 and 13), the Trade Union and Labour Relations (Consolidation) Act  1992 (c. 52) , or the Social Security Contributions and Benefits Act  1992 (c. 4) ; provide for the provisions of specified agreements to have effect in place of provisions of the regulations to such extent and in such circumstances as may be specified.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 249}, {"enrichment_value" : "Without prejudice to the generality of this section, the regulations may make any provision in relation to employees which appears to the Secretary of State to be necessary or expedient— for the purpose of implementing Council Directive  99/70/EC  on the framework agreement on fixed-term work in its application to terms and conditions of employment; for the purpose of dealing with any matter arising out of or related to the United Kingdom’s obligations under that Directive; for the purpose of any matter dealt with by the framework agreement or for the purpose of applying the provisions of the framework agreement to any matter relating to fixed term workers.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 250}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Department for Employment and Learning shall make regulations— for the purpose of securing that employees in fixed-term employment are treated, for such purposes and to such extent as the regulations may specify, no less favourably than employees in permanent employment, and for the purpose of preventing abuse arising from the use of successive periods of fixed-term employment.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 251}, {"enrichment_value" : "The regulations may— specify classes of employee who are to be taken to be, or not to be, in fixed-term employment; specify classes of employee who are to be taken to be, or not to be, in permanent employment; specify circumstances in which employees in fixed-term employment are to be taken to be, or not to be, treated less favourably than employees in permanent employment; specify circumstances in which periods of fixed-term employment are to be taken to be, or not to be, successive; specify circumstances in which fixed-term employment is to have effect as permanent employment; make provision which has effect in relation to employees in fixed-term employment generally or provision which has effect only in relation to specified classes of employee in fixed-term employment.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 252}, {"enrichment_value" : "shall deal with the application in accordance with regulations made by the Secretary of State, and", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 263}, {"enrichment_value" : "The regulations may— confer jurisdiction (including exclusive jurisdiction) on industrial tribunals; provide for specified obligations not to apply in specified circumstances; make provision about notices or information to be given, evidence to be produced and other procedures to be followed; amend, apply with or without modifications, or make provision similar to any provision of— the Employment Rights (Northern Ireland) Order 1996 ( S.I. 1996/1919 ) (including, in particular, Parts 6, 11 and 15), the Trade Union and Labour Relations (Northern Ireland) Order 1995 ( S.I. 1995/1980 (N.I. 12) ), or the Social Security Contributions and Benefits (Northern Ireland) Act  1992 (c. 7) ; provide for the provisions of specified agreements to have effect in place of provisions of the regulations to such extent and in such circumstances as may be specified.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 253}, {"enrichment_value" : "Without prejudice to the generality of this section, the regulations may make any provision in relation to employees which appears to the Department for Employment and Learning to be necessary or expedient— for the purpose of implementing Council Directive  99/70/EC  on the framework agreement on fixed-term work in its application to terms and conditions of employment; for the purpose of dealing with any matter arising out of or related to the United Kingdom’s obligations under that Directive; for the purpose of any matter dealt with by the framework agreement or for the purpose of applying the provisions of the framework agreement to any matter relating to fixed term workers.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 254}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under this section shall not be made unless a draft of them has been laid before and approved by resolution of the Northern Ireland Assembly.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[6]/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 255}, {"enrichment_value" : "A qualifying employee may apply to his employer for a change in his terms and conditions of employment if— the change relates to— the hours he is required to work, the times when he is required to work, where, as between his home and a place of business of his employer, he is required to work, or such other aspect of his terms and conditions of employment as the Secretary of State may specify by regulations, and his purpose in applying for the change is to enable him to care for someone who, at the time of application, is a child in respect of whom he satisfies such conditions as to relationship as the Secretary of State may specify by regulations.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 256}, {"enrichment_value" : "An application under this section must— state that it is such an application, specify the change applied for and the date on which it is proposed the change should become effective, explain what effect, if any, the employee thinks making the change applied for would have on his employer and how, in his opinion, any such effect might be dealt with, and explain how the employee meets, in respect of the child concerned, the conditions as to relationship mentioned in subsection (1)(b).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 257}, {"enrichment_value" : "An application under this section must be made before the fourteenth day before the day on which the child concerned reaches the age of six or, if disabled, eighteen.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 258}, {"enrichment_value" : "If an employee has made an application under this section, he may not make a further application under this section to the same employer before the end of the period of twelve months beginning with the date on which the previous application was made.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 259}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by regulations make provision about— the form of applications under this section, and when such an application is to be taken as made.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 260}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by order substitute a different age for the first of the ages specified in subsection (3).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 261}, {"enrichment_value" : "satisfies such conditions as to duration of employment as the Secretary of State may specify by regulations, and", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[8]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[8]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 262}, {"enrichment_value" : "shall only refuse the application because he considers that one or more of the following grounds applies— the burden of additional costs, detrimental effect on ability to meet customer demand, inability to re-organise work among existing staff, inability to recruit additional staff, detrimental impact on quality, detrimental impact on performance, insufficiency of work during the periods the employee proposes to work, planned structural changes, and such other grounds as the Secretary of State may specify by regulations.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[1]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 264}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1)(a) shall include— provision for the holding of a meeting between the employer and the employee to discuss an application under section 80F within twenty eight days after the date the application is made; provision for the giving by the employer to the employee of notice of his decision on the application within fourteen days after the date of the meeting under paragraph (a); provision for notice under paragraph (b) of a decision to refuse the application to state the grounds for the decision; provision for the employee to have a right, if he is dissatisfied with the employer’s decision, to appeal against it within fourteen days after the date on which notice under paragraph (b) is given; provision about the procedure for exercising the right of appeal under paragraph (d), including provision requiring the employee to set out the grounds of appeal; provision for notice under paragraph (b) to include such information as the regulations may specify relating to the right of appeal under paragraph (d); provision for the holding, within fourteen days after the date on which notice of appeal is given by the employee, of a meeting between the employer and the employee to discuss the appeal; provision for the employer to give the employee notice of his decision on any appeal within fourteen days after the date of the meeting under paragraph (g); provision for notice under paragraph (h) of a decision to dismiss an appeal to state the grounds for the decision; provision for a statement under paragraph (c) or (i) to contain a sufficient explanation of the grounds for the decision; provision for the employee to have a right to be accompanied at meetings under paragraph (a) or (g) by a person of such description as the regulations may specify; provision for postponement in relation to any meeting under paragraph (a) or (g) which a companion under paragraph (k) is not available to attend; provision in relation to companions under paragraph (k) corresponding to section 10(6) and (7) of the Employment Relations Act  1999 (c. 26)  (right to paid time off to act as companion, etc.); provision, in relation to the rights under paragraphs (k) and (l), for the application (with or without modification) of sections 11 to 13 of the Employment Relations Act 1999 (provisions ancillary to right to be accompanied under section 10 of that Act).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 265}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under subsection (1)(a) may include— provision for any requirement of the regulations not to apply where an application is disposed of by agreement or withdrawn; provision for extension of a time limit where the employer and employee agree, or in such other circumstances as the regulations may specify; provision for applications to be treated as withdrawn in specified circumstances; and may make different provision for different cases.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 266}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by order amend subsection (2).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 267}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employee who makes an application under section 80F may present a complaint to an employment tribunal— that his employer has failed in relation to the application to comply with section 80G(1), or that a decision by his employer to reject the application was based on incorrect facts.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 268}, {"enrichment_value" : "No complaint under this section may be made in respect of an application which has been disposed of by agreement or withdrawn.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 269}, {"enrichment_value" : "In the case of an application which has not been disposed of by agreement or withdrawn, no complaint under this section may be made until the employer— notifies the employee of a decision to reject the application on appeal, or commits a breach of regulations under section 80G(1)(a) of such description as the Secretary of State may specify by regulations.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 270}, {"enrichment_value" : "No complaint under this section may be made in respect of failure to comply with provision included in regulations under subsection (1)(a) of section 80G because of subsection (2)(k), (l) or (m) of that section.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 271}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employment tribunal shall not consider a complaint under this section unless it is presented— before the end of the period of three months beginning with the relevant date, or within such further period as the tribunal considers reasonable in a case where it is satisfied that it was not reasonably practicable for the complaint to be presented before the end of that period of three months.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[3]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 272}, {"enrichment_value" : "Meetings must be conducted in a manner that enables both employer and employee to explain their cases.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[3]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[3]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 344}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where an employment tribunal finds a complaint under section 80H well-founded it shall make a declaration to that effect and may— make an order for reconsideration of the application, and make an award of compensation to be paid by the employer to the employee.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 273}, {"enrichment_value" : "The amount of compensation shall be such amount, not exceeding the permitted maximum, as the tribunal considers just and equitable in all the circumstances.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 274}, {"enrichment_value" : "For the purposes of subsection (2), the permitted maximum is such number of weeks' pay as the Secretary of State may specify by regulations.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 275}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where an employment tribunal makes an order under subsection (1)(a), section 80G, and the regulations under that section, shall apply as if the application had been made on the date of the order.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:part/ns:section[4]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 276}, {"enrichment_value" : "An employee who is dismissed shall be regarded for the purposes of this Part as unfairly dismissed if the reason (or, if more than one, the principal reason) for the dismissal is that the employee— made (or proposed to make) an application under section 80F, exercised (or proposed to exercise) a right conferred on him under section 80G, brought proceedings against the employer under section 80H, or alleged the existence of any circumstance which would constitute a ground for bringing such proceedings.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[7]/ns:subsection[4]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 277}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations may make provision for or in connection with imposing, at a time when— a person (“the claimant”) who— is under the age of 60, and has a partner who is also under that age, is entitled to a benefit to which this section applies at a higher rate referable to his partner, and prescribed circumstances exist, a requirement for the partner to take part in a work-focused interview as a condition of the benefit continuing to be payable to the claimant at that rate.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[9]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[9]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 278}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under this section may, in particular, make provision— for securing, where the partner of the claimant would otherwise be required to take part in work-focused interviews relating to two or more benefits— that the partner is required instead to take part in only one such interview; and that the interview is capable of counting for the purposes of all those benefits; in a case where the claimant has more than one partner, for determining which of those partners is required to take part in the work-focused interview or requiring each of them to take part in such an interview; for determining the persons by whom work-focused interviews are to be conducted; conferring power on such persons or the designated authority to determine when and where work-focused interviews are to take place (including power in prescribed circumstances to determine that they are to take place in the homes of those being interviewed); prescribing the circumstances in which partners attending work-focused interviews are to be regarded as having or not having taken part in them; for securing that if— a partner who has been notified of a requirement to take part in a work-focused interview fails to take part in it, and it is not shown (by him or by the claimant), within the prescribed period, that he had good cause for that failure, the amount payable to the claimant in respect of the benefit in relation to which the requirement applied is to be reduced by the specified amount until the specified time; prescribing— matters which are or are not to be taken into account in determining whether a partner does or does not have good cause for any failure to comply with the regulations; or circumstances in which a partner is or is not to be regarded as having or not having good cause for any such failure.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[9]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[9]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 279}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under this section may, in relation to a reduction under subsection (4)(f), provide— for the amount of the reduction to be calculated in the first instance by reference to such amount as may be prescribed; for the amount as so calculated to be restricted, in prescribed circumstances, to the prescribed extent; where the claimant is entitled to two or more benefits in relation to each of which a requirement to take part in a work-focused interview applied, for determining the extent to, and the order in, which those benefits are to be reduced in order to give effect to the reduction required in his case.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[9]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[9]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 280}, {"enrichment_value" : "After the notice of a determination under this paragraph has been served the determination shall not be altered except in accordance with this paragraph or on appeal.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 294}, {"enrichment_value" : "If it is discovered by an officer of the Board authorised by the Board for the purposes of this paragraph that the amount of a penalty determined under this paragraph is or has become insufficient, the officer may make a determination in a further amount so that the penalty is set at the amount which, in his opinion, is correct or appropriate.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 295}, {"enrichment_value" : "Regulations under this section may provide that any requirement to take part in a work-focused interview that would otherwise apply to a partner by virtue of the regulations— is, in any prescribed circumstances, either not to apply or not to apply until the specified time; is not to apply if the designated authority determines that such an interview would not be of assistance to him or appropriate in the circumstances; is not to apply until such time as the designated authority determines (if that authority determines that such an interview would not be of assistance to him or appropriate in the circumstances until that time); and the regulations may make provision for treating a partner to whom any such requirement does not apply, or does not apply until a particular time, as having complied with that requirement to such extent and for such purposes as are specified.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[9]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[9]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 281}, {"enrichment_value" : "In this section— “couple” means a married or unmarried couple (within the meaning of Part 7 of the Contributions and Benefits Act); “designated authority” means such of the following as may be specified, namely— the Secretary of State, a person providing services to the Secretary of State, a local authority, and a person providing services to, or authorised to exercise any function of, a local authority; “partner” means a person who is a member of the same couple as the claimant; “specified” means prescribed by or determined in accordance with regulations; and “work-focused interview” has the same meaning as in section 2A above.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[9]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:section[9]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 282}, {"enrichment_value" : "No order may be made under this Act unless a draft of the order has been laid before and approved by resolution of each House of Parliament.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 283}, {"enrichment_value" : "No regulations may be made under section 30, 31, 32, 33 or 45 unless a draft of the regulations has been laid before and approved by resolution of each House of Parliament.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 284}, {"enrichment_value" : "A statutory instrument containing regulations under any other provision of this Act shall be subject to annulment in pursuance of a resolution of either House of Parliament.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[1]/ns:subsection[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 285}, {"enrichment_value" : "There shall be paid out of money provided by Parliament— any expenses incurred by a Minister of the Crown or government department in consequence of this Act, and any increase attributable to this Act in the sums so provided under any other Act.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 286}, {"enrichment_value" : "There shall be paid into the Consolidated Fund any increase attributable to this Act in the sums payable into that Fund under any other Act.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[2]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 287}, {"enrichment_value" : "This Act may be cited as the Employment Act 2002.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 288}, {"enrichment_value" : "This Act, except sections 45, 46, 51 and 52 and this section, shall come into force on such day as the Secretary of State may by order made by statutory instrument appoint, and different days may be so appointed for different purposes.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 289}, {"enrichment_value" : "An order under subsection (2) may contain such transitional provisions and savings as the Secretary of State considers necessary or expedient in connection with the coming into force of any of the provisions of this Act.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 290}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Secretary of State may by regulations make such transitional provisions and savings as he considers necessary or expedient for the purposes of or in connection with— the coming into force of section 19 or 48, or Schedule 7 so far as relating to any amendment made in consequence of either of those sections; or the operation of any enactment amended by any of those provisions during any period when the amendment is not wholly in force.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:part[4]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:section[5]/ns:subsection[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 291}, {"enrichment_value" : "Subject to sub-paragraph (2) and except where proceedings have been instituted under paragraph 5, an officer of the Board authorised by the Board for the purposes of this paragraph may make a determination— imposing a penalty under section 11 or 12, and setting it at such amount as, in his opinion, is correct or appropriate.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 292}, {"enrichment_value" : "Notice of a determination of a penalty under this paragraph shall be served on the person liable to the penalty and shall state the date on which it is issued and the time within which an appeal against the determination may be made.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 293}, {"enrichment_value" : "Part 6 of the Taxes Management Act  1970 (c. 9)  shall apply in relation to a penalty determined under paragraph 1 as if it were tax charged in an assessment and due and payable.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 297}, {"enrichment_value" : "An appeal may be brought against the determination of a penalty under paragraph 1.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 298}, {"enrichment_value" : "The provisions of the Taxes Management Act 1970 relating to appeals, except section 50(6) to (8), shall have effect in relation to an appeal against such a determination as they have effect in relation to an appeal against an assessment to tax.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 299}, {"enrichment_value" : "On an appeal by virtue of sub-paragraph (2) against the determination of a penalty under paragraph 1, the General or Special Commissioners may— if it appears to them that no penalty has been incurred, set the determination aside; if the amount determined appears to them to be appropriate, confirm the determination; if the amount determined appears to them to be excessive, reduce it to such other amount (including nil) as they consider appropriate; if the amount determined appears to them to be insufficient, increase it to such amount not exceeding the permitted maximum as they consider appropriate.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 300}, {"enrichment_value" : "An appeal from a decision of the Commissioners against the amount of a penalty which has been determined under paragraph 1 or this paragraph shall lie, at the instance of the person liable to the penalty— to the High Court, or in Scotland, to the Court of Session as the Court of Exchequer in Scotland; and on that appeal the court shall have the like jurisdiction as is conferred on the Commissioners by virtue of this paragraph.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 301}, {"enrichment_value" : "An officer of the Board authorised by the Board for the purposes of this paragraph may commence proceedings for any penalty to which sub-paragraph (1) of paragraph 1 does not apply by virtue of sub-paragraph (2) of that paragraph.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[4]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[4]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 302}, {"enrichment_value" : "Proceedings under this paragraph shall be by way of information in writing, made to the General or Special Commissioners, and upon summons issued by them to the defendant (or, in Scotland, the defender) to appear before them at a time and place stated in the summons; and they shall hear and decide each case in a summary way.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[4]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[4]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 303}, {"enrichment_value" : "Part 6 of the Taxes Management Act  1970 (c. 9)  shall apply in relation to a penalty determined in proceedings under this paragraph as if it were tax charged in an assessment and due and payable.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[4]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[4]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 304}, {"enrichment_value" : "An appeal against the determination of a penalty in proceedings under this paragraph shall lie to the High Court or, in Scotland, to the Court of Session as the Court of Exchequer in Scotland— by any party on a question of law, and by the defendant (or, in Scotland, the defender) against the amount of the penalty.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[4]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[4]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 305}, {"enrichment_value" : "On any such appeal the court may— if it appears that no penalty has been incurred, set the determination aside; if the amount determined appears to be appropriate, confirm the determination; if the amount determined appears to be excessive, reduce it to such other amount (including nil) as the court considers appropriate; if the amount determined appears to be insufficient, increase it to such amount not exceeding the permitted maximum as the court considers appropriate.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[4]/ns:subparagraph[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[4]/ns:subparagraph[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 306}, {"enrichment_value" : "Where in the opinion of the Board the liability of any person for a penalty under section 11 or 12 arises by reason of the fraud of that or any other person, proceedings for the penalty may be instituted before the High Court or, in Scotland, the Court of Session as the Court of Exchequer in Scotland.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[5]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[5]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 307}, {"enrichment_value" : "Subject to sub-paragraph (3), proceedings under this paragraph shall be instituted— in England and Wales, in the name of the Attorney General, and in Scotland, in the name of the Advocate General for Scotland.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[5]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[5]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 308}, {"enrichment_value" : "Sub-paragraph (2) shall not prevent proceedings under this paragraph being instituted in England and Wales under the Crown Proceedings Act  1947 (c. 44)  by and in the name of the Board as an authorised department for the purposes of that Act.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[5]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[5]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 309}, {"enrichment_value" : "Any proceedings under this paragraph instituted in England and Wales shall be deemed to be civil proceedings by the Crown within the meaning of Part 2 of the Crown Proceedings Act 1947.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[5]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[5]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 310}, {"enrichment_value" : "If in proceedings under this paragraph the court does not find that fraud is proved but considers that the person concerned is nevertheless liable to a penalty, the court may determine a penalty notwithstanding that, but for the opinion of the Board as to fraud, the penalty would not have been a matter for the court.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[5]/ns:subparagraph[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[5]/ns:subparagraph[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 311}, {"enrichment_value" : "The Board may in their discretion mitigate any penalty under section 11 or 12, or stay or compound any proceedings for a penalty, and may also, after judgment, further mitigate or entirely remit the penalty.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[6]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[6]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 312}, {"enrichment_value" : "A penalty under section 11 or 12 may be determined by an officer of the Board, or proceedings for the penalty may be commenced before the Commissioners or the court, at any time within six years after the date on which the penalty was incurred or began to be incurred.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[7]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[7]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 313}, {"enrichment_value" : "After paragraph (p) of section 178(2) of the Finance Act  1989 (c. 26)  (setting rates of interest) there shall be inserted— q paragraph 8 of Schedule 1 to the Employment Act 2002. paragraph 8 of Schedule 1 to the Employment Act 2002.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[8]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[8]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 314}, {"enrichment_value" : "A penalty under section 11 or 12 shall carry interest at the rate applicable under section 178 of the Finance Act 1989 from the date on which it becomes due and payable until payment.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[8]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[8]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 315}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employer must set out in writing the employee’s alleged conduct or characteristics, or other circumstances, which lead him to contemplate dismissing or taking disciplinary action against the employee.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 316}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employer must send the statement or a copy of it to the employee and invite the employee to attend a meeting to discuss the matter.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[1]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 317}, {"enrichment_value" : "The meeting must take place before action is taken, except in the case where the disciplinary action consists of suspension.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 318}, {"enrichment_value" : "The meeting must not take place unless— the employer has informed the employee what the basis was for including in the statement under paragraph 1(1) the ground or grounds given in it, and the employee has had a reasonable opportunity to consider his response to that information.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 319}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employee must take all reasonable steps to attend the meeting.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 320}, {"enrichment_value" : "After the meeting, the employer must inform the employee of his decision and notify him of the right to appeal against the decision if he is not satisfied with it.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 321}, {"enrichment_value" : "If the employee does wish to appeal, he must inform the employer.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 322}, {"enrichment_value" : "If the employee informs the employer of his wish to appeal, the employer must invite him to attend a further meeting.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 323}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employee must take all reasonable steps to attend the meeting.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 324}, {"enrichment_value" : "After the appeal meeting, the employer must inform the employee of his final decision.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[5]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[5]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 325}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employer must— set out in writing— the employee’s alleged misconduct which has led to the dismissal, what the basis was for thinking at the time of the dismissal that the employee was guilty of the alleged misconduct, and the employee’s right to appeal against dismissal, and send the statement or a copy of it to the employee.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 326}, {"enrichment_value" : "If the employee does wish to appeal, he must inform the employer.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 327}, {"enrichment_value" : "If the employee informs the employer of his wish to appeal, the employer must invite him to attend a meeting.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 328}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employee must take all reasonable steps to attend the meeting.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 329}, {"enrichment_value" : "After the appeal meeting, the employer must inform the employee of his final decision.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[1]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 330}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employee must set out the grievance in writing and send the statement or a copy of it to the employer.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 331}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employer must invite the employee to attend a meeting to discuss the grievance.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 332}, {"enrichment_value" : "The meeting must not take place unless— the employee has informed the employer what the basis for the grievance was when he made the statement under paragraph 6, and the employer has had a reasonable opportunity to consider his response to that information.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 333}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employee must take all reasonable steps to attend the meeting.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 334}, {"enrichment_value" : "After the meeting, the employer must inform the employee of his decision as to his response to the grievance and notify him of the right to appeal against the decision if he is not satisfied with it.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 335}, {"enrichment_value" : "If the employee does wish to appeal, he must inform the employer.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 336}, {"enrichment_value" : "If the employee informs the employer of his wish to appeal, the employer must invite him to attend a further meeting.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 337}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employee must take all reasonable steps to attend the meeting.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 338}, {"enrichment_value" : "After the appeal meeting, the employer must inform the employee of his final decision.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[1]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 339}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employee must— set out in writing— the grievance, and the basis for it, and send the statement or a copy of it to the employer.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[1]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 340}, {"enrichment_value" : "The employer must set out his response in writing and send the statement or a copy of it to the employee.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[2]/ns:chapter[2]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 341}, {"enrichment_value" : "Each step and action under the procedure must be taken without unreasonable delay.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[3]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[3]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 342}, {"enrichment_value" : "In the case of appeal meetings which are not the first meeting, the employer should, as far as is reasonably practicable, be represented by a more senior manager than attended the first meeting (unless the most senior manager attended that meeting).", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[3]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[3]/ns:paragraph[3]/ns:subparagraph[3]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 345}, {"enrichment_value" : "it is the intention of the employee that the disclosure should constitute the raising of the matter with his employer as a grievance.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[4]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[2]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:part[4]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:subparagraph[2]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 346}, {"enrichment_value" : "Section 3(3) of the Social Security Act  1998 (c. 14)  (which is superseded by paragraphs 2 and 3) shall cease to have effect.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[6]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[4]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[6]/ns:hcontainer[1]/ns:paragraph[4]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 347}, {"enrichment_value" : "is required by the Secretary of State or the Northern Ireland Department in order to assess policy relating to such schemes.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[6]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_start": "ns:act/ns:body/ns:hcontainer/ns:hcontainer[6]/ns:hcontainer[2]/ns:paragraph[2]/ns:content/ns:p[2]/ns:mod/ns:quotedStructure/ns:section/ns:subsection[1]/ns:paragraph[2]", "extent_char_end": null, "extent_char_start": null}]}, "enrichment_id" : 348}, {"enrichment_value" : "No obligation as to secrecy imposed by statute or otherwise on a person employed in relation to the Inland Revenue shall prevent any such information obtained or held in connection with the assessment or collection of income tax from being disclosed to— the Secretary of State; the Northern Ireland Department; or an officer of either of them authorised to receive such information for the purposes of this section.", "enrichment_def_id" : 1, "enrichment_extent" : {"type": "xml", "sections": [{"extent_end": "ns: